.TH PS 1 "May, 2026"

.SH NAME
\fBps\fP \- show running processes

.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBps\fP [\fB\-A\fP] [\fB\-T\fP] [\fIformat\fP]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Shows a table of information about running processes.

.TP
.B \-A
Show all processes from all users and regardless of whether
they have an associated terminal or not.

.TP
.B \-T
Include threads in the output.

.PP
When a \fIformat\fP string is provided, the full command line for
each process is shown, and the output is otherwise modified as
follows:

.TP
.B a
Show processes from all users.

.TP
.B u
Show additional columns, including \fBUSER\fP and a few others.

.TP
.B x
Show processes with or without associated terminals.

.PP
Other format characters are silently ignored.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR top (1),
.BR libtoaru_procfs (3)
